curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/6261' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM2555", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM2555 is a single channel power distribution  switch. The switch operates from a wide range of  2.2V to 5.5V supply voltage, and is controlled by the  EN pin. It can be used in USB power distribution  applications.   A 95mΩ low RON N-MOSFET is integrated. The small  size and quiescent current make the device very  suitable for space limited, battery-powered applications.  A number of protection features are provided in the  device including soft-start, current limit of 1.85A and  thermal shutdown. The internal reverse-voltage  function will protect devices on the input side of the  switch.  The SGM2555 is available in a Green TDFN-2×2-6L  package and is rated over the -40℃ to +85℃  temperature range.  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/6262' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM2555", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES    Input Voltage Range: 2.2V to 5.5V    On-Resistance: 95mΩ (TYP)     Continuous Current: 1.1A    Current Limit: 1.85A    Quiescent Current: 19μA    Shutdown Current: 1μA (MAX)    Full Set of Protections   Soft-Start    Under-Voltage Lockout for VIN   No Reversed Leakage Current   Thermal Shutdown    Evaluated to IEC 60950-1, Ed 2, Am1, Annex CC,   Test Program 1 with CB Report    Available in a Green TDFN-2×2-6L Package    "}'
